Sentencas: This study is conducted to evaluate the electrochemical performance of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) fabricated with La0.65Ca0.35FeO3-delta (LCaF)-based cathodes.
Titulo: La0.65Ca0.35FeO3-δ as a novel Sr- and Co-free cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: LCaF has a high oxygen permeation flux Joe compared with typical mixed ionic-electronic conductors composed of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCoF) oxygen permeation membranes.
Titulo: La0.65Ca0.35FeO3-δ as a novel Sr- and Co-free cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: LCaF powder with a high specific surface area (S-BET = 9.62 m(2) g(-1)) and high crystallinity is prepared by a citrate-based liquid mixing technique.
Titulo: La0.65Ca0.35FeO3-δ as a novel Sr- and Co-free cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The anode-supported cell with an LCaF cathode has a high power density of 3.4 W cm(-2) at 800 degrees C under a terminal voltage of 0.7 V. The performance of the cells is further enhanced by preparing a composite cathode of LCaF-Gd-doped CeO2 (GDC).
Titulo: La0.65Ca0.35FeO3-δ as a novel Sr- and Co-free cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power density of the cell fabricated with the LCaF-GDC composite cathode reaches 4.4 W cm(-2) at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: La0.65Ca0.35FeO3-δ as a novel Sr- and Co-free cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Compared with a cell with a cathode prepared from commercial La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCoF), this cell exhibites superior electrochemical performance at all temperatures within the range of 500-800 degrees C.
Titulo: La0.65Ca0.35FeO3-δ as a novel Sr- and Co-free cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The high electronic and ionic conductivity of LCaF is presumed to have contributed to the superior electrochemical performance of the anodesupported cells with LCaF-based cathodes.
Titulo: La0.65Ca0.35FeO3-δ as a novel Sr- and Co-free cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: LCaF is found to be a promising candidate as a cathode material for SOFCs.
Titulo: La0.65Ca0.35FeO3-δ as a novel Sr- and Co-free cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells
